# Roboguide Rule

Apply when specifying, reviewing, or authoring Roboguide workcells and offline programs.

## Products

- Roboguide (base) - generic offline simulator.
- HandlingPRO - pick-and-place cells.
- PalletPRO - palletizing.
- WeldPRO - arc welding.
- iRPickTool - high-speed picking with vision.
- PaintPRO - paint application (less common in our practice).

## Layout

- Workcells live in `tools/roboguide/workcells/<customer_or_project>/`. LFS-tracked and `.cursorignored`.
- Export directories (generated) live in `tools/roboguide/exports/` and are gitignored.
- Per-cell README documents: robot model + payload, reach, tool, frames, fixtures, controller version simulated.

## Simulation vs reality

- The virtual controller matches the real controller's major version. Note any diffs.
- TP programs exported from Roboguide land in `customer_programs/<c>/current/` after QA review, NOT directly in a Roboguide folder.
- Positions taught offline must be validated on hardware; mark them `UNTESTED` in comments until verified.

## Cycle-time estimates

- Cite Roboguide's cycle-time reporter output in spec documents, but always note the simulation-vs-real delta observed historically for that cell.

## Anti-patterns

- Treating Roboguide-generated positions as production-ready without on-robot touch-up.
- Committing binary workcell files (`.fpc`, `.sit`, `.wsp`) outside LFS.
- Using Roboguide as the source of truth for fieldbus timing (it is not).

## PC SDK interop

- PC SDK applications (Windows .NET) live under `tools/pcsdk/` (not pre-scaffolded).
- Always version the PC SDK runtime used; older PC SDK installs lose behavior on newer V9.x controllers.

Canon reference for offline patterns: `fanuc_dataset/normalized/articles/ONE_offline_programming_workflow.md`.
